princeton_ansible.title: Create draft playbook for checkmk agent

comments.body:
Port 8000 is now open to the VPN. Since the `Fetch fresh monitoring data from host` task is connecting to `server_url: "{{ checkmk_agent_server_protocol }}://{{ checkmk_agent_server }}:{{ checkmk_agent_server_port }}/"`, I tried changing `checkmk_agent_server_port` to `8000` to see if it would connect to the Receiver. It seems that same port is used by an earlier task, which then fails:
```
TASK [checkmk.general.agent : Linux: Download Vanilla CRE agent.] *****************************************
FAILED - RETRYING: [pdc-describe-staging1.princeton.edu]: Linux: Download Vanilla CRE agent. (3 retries left).
FAILED - RETRYING: [pdc-describe-staging1.princeton.edu]: Linux: Download Vanilla CRE agent. (2 retries left).
FAILED - RETRYING: [pdc-describe-staging1.princeton.edu]: Linux: Download Vanilla CRE agent. (1 retries left).
fatal: [pdc-describe-staging1.princeton.edu]: FAILED! => {"attempts": 3, "changed": false, "dest": "/tmp/check-mk-agent_2.2.0p9-vanilla.deb", "elapsed": 0, "gid": 0, "group": "root", "mode": "0640", "msg": "Request failed: <urlopen error [Errno 111] Connection refused>", "owner": "root", "size": 4016434, "state": "file", "uid": 0, "url": "https://pulcheck-staging.princeton.edu:8000/pulmonitor/check_mk/agents/check-mk-agent_2.2.0p9-1_all.deb"}
```
I tried to set separate ports for the two tasks, by copying the `agent` role into our repo (on the branch) so I could modify it and changing the variable in the `Fetch fresh monitoring data from host` task to be `checkmk_agent_receiver_port`,. I set our playbook to run the local copy of the role, and set the two port variables separately:
```
    - checkmk_agent_server_port: 443
    - checkmk_agent_receiver_port: 8000
```
The `Download Vanilla CRE agent` task went back to passing, but the `Fetch fresh monitoring data` task still failed, though it returned a different error:
```
TASK [../../roles/checkmk_agent : Fetch fresh monitoring data from host.] *********************************
FAILED - RETRYING: [pdc-describe-staging1.princeton.edu -> localhost]: Fetch fresh monitoring data from host. (3 retries left).
FAILED - RETRYING: [pdc-describe-staging1.princeton.edu -> localhost]: Fetch fresh monitoring data from host. (2 retries left).
FAILED - RETRYING: [pdc-describe-staging1.princeton.edu -> localhost]: Fetch fresh monitoring data from host. (1 retries left).
fatal: [pdc-describe-staging1.princeton.edu -> localhost]: FAILED! => {"attempts": 3, "changed": false, "msg": "-1 - Error calling API Details: Request failed: <urlopen error timed out>"}
```
I also tried setting `checkmk_agent_tls: 'true'`, which made a different task fail:
```
TASK [checkmk.general.agent : Linux: Register Agent for TLS.] *********************************************
fatal: [pdc-describe-staging1.princeton.edu]: FAILED! => {"censored": "the output has been hidden due to the fact that 'no_log: true' was specified for this result", "changed": true}
```

As of 0c700761bc0ba43b4a04b85a146e5e7260eddf7e the playbook successfully installs the agent and creates a host record on the checkMK server. It still fails on the `Fetch fresh monitoring data from host` task, but we get a new error:
```
fatal: [ansible-tower2.princeton.edu -> localhost]: FAILED! => {"attempts": 3, "changed": false, "msg": "-1 - Error calling API Details: Connection failure: Remote end closed connection without response"}
```
Ansible seems to be delegating this task to `localhost` . . . maybe that is related to the failure? 

I tried to register the new host from the command line with:
```
[pulsys@ansible-tower2 ~]$ sudo cmk-agent-ctl register --hostname ansible-tower2.princeton.edu --server pulcheck-staging1.princeton.edu:8000 --site pulmonitor --user troubleshooting --password ***REDACTED***
```
which got me this:
```
Do you want to establish this connection? [Y/n]
> y
Registration complete.
```
and the registration went into the list of pending changes. So maybe the host creation is also getting stuck in pending changes and the handler that activates pending changes isn't running or is failing, and that's causing this issue? Even when I activated the pending changes manually, the new host showed up in the folder I set, but the agent connection fails with `Communication failed: [Errno 113] No route to host`.
